flowRoot.flowPara: Adds the signed offset to the contents of register rs1, treating it as a memory address. Retrieves a little-endian 16-bit value from memory at that address, and zero-extends it. The result is placed in register rd.

In this example, the little-endian layout in memory at address 0908AAF0 is 76 3A C1 C5. The address to access is 0908AAF2, which contains the little-endian bytes C1 C5. The corresponding value is C5C1. When zero-extended to 32 bits, this is 0000C5C1.
